==English==

===Etymology===
First attested around 1472. From {{inh|en|enm|absurdite}},<ref name=RHD>{{R:RHCD|page=7}}</ref> then from either {{bor|en|frm|absurdité}}, or from {{bor|en|LL.|absurditas||dissonance, incongruity}}, from {{der|en|la|absurdus}} {{suffix|la||itas|gloss2=quality, state, degree|nocat=1}}.<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=8}}</ref><ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=10}}</ref> Equivalent to {{suffix|en|absurd|ity}}.

